\f0\fs24 \cf0 Elena saw the village lights long before they reached the gate. The homecoming was nothing like she had imagined during all those cold nights on the road. The houses looked smaller, the streets narrower, and the faces older.\
\
Her mother stood in the doorway, lantern raised, squinting into the darkness. When recognition came, the lantern nearly fell from her hands. No words were needed. Elena stepped inside and the door closed behind her, shutting out the wind and the long months of absence.}
